/*
  About section — most layout/visual styling still lives in About.jsx as
  inline styles (matching Hero.tsx / Projects.tsx convention). This module
  now also holds the interactive states that were previously implemented as
  inline onMouseEnter/onMouseLeave JS handlers on individual elements.

  Why move them here: those handlers ran a setState-free style mutation on
  every mouse event, which works but (a) can't be reused, (b) doesn't get
  GPU-accelerated transition batching the way a CSS class swap does, and
  (c) made every interactive element's JSX noisy with two extra props.
  Functionally identical result, fewer moving parts.
*/

